item.title: Lecture 4
item.description: Lecture 4 Video : C Part 1 Slides : C Part 1 Compilation The way c programs are built. Source file $ gcc -o hello hello.c Preprocessor Collects .c and .h into .i file. Compiler Converts .i file into assembly language file .s. Assembler Converts .s into object file .o. Encoded instruction and data bit strings. Contains unresolved symbols. Link Editor Resolves unresolved symbols.
